---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About efficientAItools"
  description="Learn about efficientAItools.com — a collection of free, privacy-focused online tools built for productivity."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <span>About</span>
      </div>
      <h1>About efficientAItools</h1>
      <p>Building simple, private, free online tools — one utility at a time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-content">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        efficientAItools.com was created to solve a simple problem: most online tools are cluttered with ads, 
        require sign-ups, or upload your files to unknown servers. We believe utilities should be 
        <strong>free, private, and fast</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Why We're Different</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Upload Required</strong> — All PDF and image processing happens right in your browser. Your files never leave your device.</li>
        <li><strong>No Sign-Up</strong> — Every tool is ready to use the moment you open the page. No accounts, no emails, no spam.</li>
        <li><strong>Ad-Free Experience</strong> — Clean, distraction-free interfaces. We don't sell your attention.</li>
        <li><strong>Always Improving</strong> — We're constantly adding new tools and improving existing ones based on user feedback.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Sustain</h2>
      <p>
        Some tools have a premium tier for advanced features (like our Math Worksheet Generator's answer keys). 
        These optional upgrades fund the development and hosting of all our free tools. 
        We never paywall basic functionality.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have a suggestion? Found a bug? Want a new tool? We'd love to hear from you.
        <a href="/contact/">Drop us a message</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
